---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service | HIIT Workout Timer | AI Fitcopilot"
  description="Terms of service for HIIT Workout Timer and AI Fitcopilot. Review the terms governing use of our interval timer apps and services."
  canonicalUrl={new URL('/terms', Astro.url.origin).href}
>
  <div class="relative min-h-screen overflow-x-hidden text-white selection:bg-orange-light selection:text-black">
    <main class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-24">
      <h1 class="mb-8 font-heading text-4xl font-bold text-white">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="mb-8 text-sm text-white/60">Last updated: March 2025</p>

      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8 text-white/90">
        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-white">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p>
            By accessing or using HIIT Workout Timer, Sync-60, AI Fitcopilot, and related services (&quot;we&quot;, &quot;our&quot;, or &quot;the Service&quot;),
            you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, do not use the Service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-white">2. Description of the Service</h2>
          <p class="mb-4">
            We provide interval timer apps and fitness tools, including but not limited to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
            <li>Interval timer protocols (Tabata, AMRAP, EMOM, Daily Warm-Up, and others)</li>
            <li>Workout tracking and activity history</li>
            <li>Account features including sign-in via email, Google, or Apple</li>
            <li>Programs, challenges, and exercise content</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-white">3. Account and Registration</h2>
          <p class="mb-4">
            You may create an account to access certain features. When you register, you may use email and password,
            or sign in with Google or Apple. You are responsible for maintaining the security of your credentials.
            You must provide accurate information and update it as needed.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our use of your account data is governed by our
            <a href="/privacy" class="text-orange-400 underline hover:text-orange-300">Privacy Policy</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-white">4. User Conduct and Prohibited Uses</h2>
          <p class="mb-4">You agree not to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
            <li>Use the Service for any unlawful purpose or in violation of applicable laws</li>
            <li>Impersonate others or misrepresent your affiliation</li>
            <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Service or its infrastructure</li>
            <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of the Service or other accounts</li>
            <li>Use the Service in a way that harms, harasses, or degrades the experience of others</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-white">5. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>
            The Service, including its design, content, software, and branding, is owned by us or our licensors.
            You may not copy, modify, distribute, or create derivative works without our prior written consent.
            You retain ownership of any content you create (e.g., workout logs) but grant us a license to use it
            as necessary to provide the Service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-white">6. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
          <p>
            The Service is provided &quot;as is&quot; and &quot;as available&quot;. We do not warrant that the Service will be
            uninterrupted, error-free, or free of harmful components. Fitness and health information is for general
            purposes only; consult a healthcare provider before starting any exercise program.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-white">7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, we are not liable for any indirect, incidental, special,
            consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of the Service. Our total liability for any
            claims related to the Service shall not exceed the amount you paid us, if any, in the twelve months
            prior to the claim.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-white">8. Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these Terms from time to time. We will notify you of material changes by posting the
            updated Terms on this page and updating the &quot;Last updated&quot; date. Your continued use of the Service
            after such changes constitutes acceptance of the new Terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-white">9. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            For questions about these Terms of Service, contact us via the support or contact channel provided
            in the app or on the main website.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-12 text-sm text-white/50">
        <a href="/privacy" class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300 mr-4">Privacy Policy</a>
        <a href="/" class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300">Return to home</a>
      </p>
    </main>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
